1
00:00:00,568 --> 00:00:02,301
I'm so jealous of Yu Jun.

2
00:00:02,302 --> 00:00:05,171
When we were little,
we just used to go to the playground...

3
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:08,440
and throw the sand that was full of ants.

4
00:00:09,343 --> 00:00:10,911
- Done.
- Good.

5
00:00:10,912 --> 00:00:12,045
It looks fun.

6
00:00:12,046 --> 00:00:13,379
I can't wait to play with sand.

7
00:00:14,047 --> 00:00:15,814
I want to play with sand too.

8
00:00:15,815 --> 00:00:17,716
This isn't for you two but for Yu Jun.

9
00:00:18,452 --> 00:00:19,485
I want to join too.

10
00:00:19,887 --> 00:00:23,089
Let's not be afraid of him crying.

11
00:00:23,223 --> 00:00:24,224
BEOMGYU should cry too.

12
00:00:24,225 --> 00:00:25,324
Should I cry even louder?

13
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,361
I cut my fingernails before I came here
to take care of him.

14
00:00:29,263 --> 00:00:30,863
I did the same.

15
00:00:31,299 --> 00:00:32,231
(The doorbell rings.)

16
00:00:32,232 --> 00:00:33,333
(Nervous)

17
00:00:34,235 --> 00:00:35,435
- It must be him.
- Shall I open the door?

18
00:00:35,436 --> 00:00:36,402
Is this it?

19
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:38,971
- What?
- It's him.

20
00:00:38,972 --> 00:00:40,706
He's with both his parents.

21
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:41,974
(Yu Jun arrives at 10:30 a.m.)

22
00:00:42,276 --> 00:00:43,443
I suddenly feel scared.

23
00:00:44,612 --> 00:00:47,313
- I'm so scared.
- I'm suddenly scared.

24
00:00:47,481 --> 00:00:49,715
(The cry of someone
who knows how arduous babysitting is)

25
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:52,218
Gather, guys.
Let's pull ourselves together and start.

26
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,787
It's the second day of babysitting.

27
00:00:55,356 --> 00:00:57,857
Let's all stay strong, not get worn out,

28
00:00:57,858 --> 00:01:00,760
and do our absolute best
to take care of Yu Jun.

29
00:01:00,761 --> 00:01:01,761
It's not like we're going on stage.

30
00:01:01,762 --> 00:01:03,462
- All right.
- TOMORROW X TOGETHER.

31
00:01:03,865 --> 00:01:06,232
We'll still be together tomorrow as well.

32
00:01:08,101 --> 00:01:09,768
- I can hear my heart race.
- What?

33
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:10,703
(Because you screamed earlier.)

34
00:01:11,939 --> 00:01:13,106
(Finally, the door opens.)

35
00:01:13,506 --> 00:01:16,442
- Hello!
- Hello!

36
00:01:16,677 --> 00:01:18,312
- Hi, Yu Jun.
- Good morning.

37
00:01:18,313 --> 00:01:19,546
It feels like he's grown bigger.

38
00:01:19,947 --> 00:01:21,014
Hi.

39
00:01:21,015 --> 00:01:22,015
You're so cute.

40
00:01:22,016 --> 00:01:23,649
He's become even cuter.

41
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:25,351
His cheeks look a bit chubbier.

42
00:01:26,053 --> 00:01:27,720
Please leave him with us
and have some food.

43
00:01:28,088 --> 00:01:29,355
- Come here.
- Say bye to your parents.

44
00:01:29,356 --> 00:01:30,389
Take care.

45
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:31,390
- Say bye.
- Say goodbye.

46
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:32,491
(Already time to say goodbye)

47
00:01:32,492 --> 00:01:34,460
- He's already tearing up.
- Say goodbye.

48
00:01:34,995 --> 00:01:37,463
"I love you, Daddy."

49
00:01:37,464 --> 00:01:39,031
- "I love you."
- Let's go.

50
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,900
(Don't let him notice
that his parents are gone.)

51
00:01:40,901 --> 00:01:42,134
Let's go play!

52
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:43,923
(The second day of babysitting begins.)

53
00:01:43,924 --> 00:01:45,871
Goodbye. Play airplane!

54
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,041
- Look at this sand!
- He's spilling water.

55
00:01:48,042 --> 00:01:49,342
Look what I have.

56
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,277
Yu Jun spilled water.

57
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:52,711
Sand.

58
00:01:52,712 --> 00:01:54,780
(Already tough from the start)

59
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:55,848
Yu Jun!

60
00:01:56,416 --> 00:01:58,183
- "Mom."
- You miss your mommy?

61
00:01:58,386 --> 00:02:00,419
Are you sad you spilled your water?

62
00:02:03,323 --> 00:02:04,255
Come here.

63
00:02:04,957 --> 00:02:05,925
Good boy.

64
00:02:05,926 --> 00:02:08,128
(He's upset since his mom's gone,
and now he's even spilled his water.)

65
00:02:08,829 --> 00:02:10,430
Look! It looks so fun!

66
00:02:10,431 --> 00:02:11,964
(The first way to soothe Yu Jun)

67
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,834
(Just hold him in your arms
and start running.)

68
00:02:15,769 --> 00:02:18,804
- Oh, my.
- "Daddy, I love you."

69
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:21,941
"Mom, Dad."

70
00:02:21,942 --> 00:02:23,876
(Improvising a melody)

71
00:02:24,411 --> 00:02:28,114
(You can easily improvise a song
when babysitting.)

72
00:02:28,115 --> 00:02:30,248
We should start the sand play right away.

73
00:02:30,249 --> 00:02:31,785
Let's go straight
into the dopamine-boosting part.

74
00:02:31,885 --> 00:02:34,386
(Putting in the sand)

75
00:02:34,387 --> 00:02:38,090
(Singing)

76
00:02:38,091 --> 00:02:41,160
(Random singing)

77
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:44,263
(More singing)

78
00:02:44,264 --> 00:02:46,699
A, B, C, D, E, F, G

79
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:49,535
(A veteran singer's
smooth song transition)

80
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:54,007
(Subtitles will be off just for now.)

81
00:02:54,008 --> 00:02:54,941
Oh, my.

82
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,710
The cherry blossoms are really pretty.

83
00:02:58,211 --> 00:02:59,578
As pretty as you, Yu Jun.

84
00:03:01,048 --> 00:03:02,215
Yu Jun, what is this?

85
00:03:02,216 --> 00:03:04,017
(Shall we try playing with sand now?)

86
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:05,918
Put some in his hand.

87
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:06,919
What is that?

88
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:08,487
What do you think it is?

89
00:03:08,822 --> 00:03:10,422
- What do you see?
- What should we do with it?

90
00:03:10,423 --> 00:03:12,559
- Isn't it fascinating?
- Do you want to play with this?

91
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,794
You want to play with this too,
but you're just holding back, right?

92
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:16,028
Gosh!

93
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:19,598
(First attempt at sand play fails)

94
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:22,969
Yu Jun, look what I have.
Do you want some rice crackers?

95
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:24,002
Shall we have some rice crackers?

96
00:03:24,104 --> 00:03:26,772
(The second way to soothe Yu Jun)

97
00:03:26,773 --> 00:03:29,842
(Trying to grab his attention
with rice crackers)

98
00:03:30,378 --> 00:03:32,211
Rice crackers!

99
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,579
Is it good? You love it, don't you?

100
00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:35,648
Let's have a rice cracker first...

101
00:03:35,649 --> 00:03:37,517
and think about what we should do.

102
00:03:37,684 --> 00:03:40,552
Let's wait until they finish setting it.

103
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:42,021
All together.

104
00:03:42,888 --> 00:03:43,889
What is that?

105
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:45,758
Yu Jun, what do you think it is?

106
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:46,892
Do you want to try?

107
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,160
Doesn't it look fascinating?

108
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,630
Yu Jun, what is this?

109
00:03:51,631 --> 00:03:52,698
What do you see?

110
00:03:52,699 --> 00:03:53,899
(Second attempt at sand play fails)

111
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,501
He doesn't want it.

112
00:03:55,502 --> 00:03:57,236
It looks like BEOMGYU has to cuddle him
for a while.

113
00:03:57,638 --> 00:03:59,439
Let's just eat some rice crackers.

114
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:01,574
He definitely stops crying
when you carry him around.

115
00:04:02,509 --> 00:04:03,609
(Woohoo)

116
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:05,411
Good boy.

117
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:08,147
(Flying around)

118
00:04:08,148 --> 00:04:09,148
He's eating the rice cracker.

119
00:04:10,217 --> 00:04:11,184
He's eating the rice cracker.

120
00:04:11,185 --> 00:04:12,852
Yu Jun is eating rice crackers!

121
00:04:12,853 --> 00:04:13,986
Guys, look.

122
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:16,121
Guys, I did it.

123
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:18,057
I don't think he's interested in this.

124
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:19,692
Right. But I find this really fun.

125
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:20,586
(Sand play hasn't started yet)

126
00:04:20,587 --> 00:04:22,028
Let's have some snacks.

127
00:04:22,229 --> 00:04:23,395
Let's all pretend this is fun.

128
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:26,442
(Third attempt at sand play)

129
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:27,499
It looks fun.

130
00:04:27,834 --> 00:04:28,700
(Playtime service)

131
00:04:28,701 --> 00:04:29,902
Doesn't it look fun?

132
00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:31,603
- Look what they have.
- Sit down first.

133
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:32,738
Come inside and sit down.

134
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:34,040
Oh, it's nice. He's not crying.

135
00:04:34,408 --> 00:04:35,708
I was wrong. Get back up.

136
00:04:37,844 --> 00:04:38,877
What's wrong?

137
00:04:39,046 --> 00:04:40,046
Should we switch off?

138
00:04:40,514 --> 00:04:41,914
- Yu Jun, peek-a-boo!
- Act naturally.

139
00:04:42,082 --> 00:04:43,049
- I love you.
- Peek-a-boo!

140
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:44,083
Act naturally.

141
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:45,484
- Peek-a-boo.
- Let me.

142
00:04:45,485 --> 00:04:46,985
(You're the chosen one of the day.)

143
00:04:46,986 --> 00:04:47,953
You like BEOMGYU?

144
00:04:48,088 --> 00:04:49,889
- BEOMGYU is the chosen one today.
- Right.

145
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:51,190
Babies often change their favorite person.

146
00:04:51,191 --> 00:04:52,291
And it's BEOMGYU today.

147
00:04:52,627 --> 00:04:54,760
(HUENINGKAI is trying to give him
the hip seat.)

148
00:04:54,761 --> 00:04:56,028
Peek-a-boo!

149
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:56,862
He's happy.

150
00:04:57,497 --> 00:04:59,665
- Are you happy?
- Good boy.

151
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,066
(Getting the hip seat on efficiently)

152
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:02,468
Good job.

153
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:04,337
(Fussing)

154
00:05:04,338 --> 00:05:06,239
Take it off quick!

155
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,707
- Take it off.
- He doesn't like it?

156
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:08,708
Take it off!

157
00:05:08,709 --> 00:05:09,675
Gosh!

158
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,411
(He barely managed to soothe him.)

159
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:13,279
(Making car sounds)

160
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,881
Peek-a-boo!

161
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,317
(BEOMGYU's merry-go-round is
back in action)

162
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,818
Peek-a-boo!

163
00:05:19,853 --> 00:05:21,887
Peek-a-boo!

164
00:05:21,888 --> 00:05:23,355
I feel sorry for BEOMGYU.

165
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:25,224
Play the "Baby Shark" song.

166
00:05:25,459 --> 00:05:26,592
That's a cure-all for sure.

167
00:05:29,730 --> 00:05:34,167
(Due to copyright issues, the audio has
been replaced with different music.)

168
00:05:35,135 --> 00:05:38,304
(Doo-roo-roo, doo-roo)

169
00:05:39,206 --> 00:05:43,509
(For reference, the Grandma Shark part is
playing right now.)

170
00:05:44,945 --> 00:05:46,979
(This is the highlight.)

171
00:05:47,481 --> 00:05:51,417
(Today's MVP duo shot)

172
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:52,918
Yu Jun, is it hot?

173
00:05:53,487 --> 00:05:54,887
BEOMGYU must be hotter.

174
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:58,958
- He's on his feet.
- He is.

175
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:01,060
Yu Jun, should I take a picture for you?

176
00:06:01,328 --> 00:06:03,296
(Hold me again.)

177
00:06:03,297 --> 00:06:04,263
Goodness.

178
00:06:04,264 --> 00:06:06,198
Gosh.

179
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,533
(The third way to soothe Yu Jun)

180
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:09,869
(Changing him into lighter clothes)

181
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,537
Carry him and walk around a bit.

182
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:14,106
Was it hot? Oh, boy.

183
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:15,141
Should we go this way?

184
00:06:15,142 --> 00:06:17,343
- Let's go this way.
- You want to check this way out?

185
00:06:17,344 --> 00:06:18,911
Good boy.

186
00:06:18,912 --> 00:06:19,779
Are you all right?

187
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,881
Even just taking one sleeve off helps,
right?

188
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:23,215
(No.)

189
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:25,818
- No?
- Okay.

190
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:26,919
Oh, it doesn't.

191
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,953
(BEOMGYU can even talk to him.)

192
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:28,921
Raise your arms.

193
00:06:28,922 --> 00:06:31,290
Was it rice clickers?

194
00:06:31,291 --> 00:06:33,993
Whatever it is called,
bring that snack now.

195
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:36,161
- Okay!
- It's okay.

196
00:06:36,162 --> 00:06:37,663
I told you to bring it quickly.

197
00:06:38,165 --> 00:06:39,932
- Here you go.
- Look what I've got!

198
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:41,567
Look at this.

199
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:42,768
(It's too late.)

200
00:06:42,936 --> 00:06:44,770
Both sleeves are off. He'll feel better.

201
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:46,472
- Does it feel better?
- You want it?

202
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,308
"I'm going to cry,
but give it to me, anyway."

203
00:06:50,177 --> 00:06:51,110
Yu Jun, want some water?

204
00:06:51,178 --> 00:06:52,945
- He must be thirsty after crying so much.
- Want some water?

205
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,114
You'll finish that quickly
and drink some water?

206
00:06:55,216 --> 00:06:56,882
- He is just stuffing it into his mouth.
- You want it?

207
00:06:56,984 --> 00:06:58,116
You want to drink it?

208
00:06:58,317 --> 00:06:59,418
You can't drink it now.

209
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,720
You want some water?

210
00:07:01,721 --> 00:07:02,855
Take your time.

211
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:05,457
We just need to take his clothes off.
We're almost there.

212
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:07,894
Guys, let's think about this differently.

213
00:07:07,895 --> 00:07:09,862
Do we have to take his clothes off?
Let's just open the window.

214
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:12,465
- What a brilliant idea.
- You're hot too, right?

215
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:14,133
(Fussing)

216
00:07:14,701 --> 00:07:17,169
We gave you water and opened the window,
so why are you crying?

217
00:07:18,071 --> 00:07:19,004
(The view is nice.)
Do you feel cooler now?

218
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,440
It is cool.

219
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:22,808
BEOMGYU is feeling cooler.

220
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,509
(Thirty minutes have passed...)

221
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:27,446
(with Yu Jun in his arms.)

222
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:32,084
(Let's appreciate BEOMGYU's beauty.
No, let's have a short break.)

223
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:34,052
My left arm is shaking.

224
00:07:34,721 --> 00:07:36,288
Put him down for now,
and if he cries, we can take turns.

225
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:37,723
- Okay.
- He is going to cry anyway.

226
00:07:37,724 --> 00:07:40,359
It's okay to cry.
Crying is nothing to be ashamed of.

227
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:42,227
- It's not.
- But at least for three minutes...

228
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:43,962
Still, it'd be better
to be a little less embarrassed.

229
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:46,098
(Two dung beetles)

230
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,869
(BEOMGYU's left arm is malfunctioning.)

231
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:54,339
(I'm smiling, but I'm not actually happy.)

232
00:07:55,108 --> 00:07:55,974
(Courageously sitting down)

233
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,342
We have to feed him, though.

234
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:00,279
(No, I'll just lie down.)

235
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,380
Lie down for a bit.

236
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:03,949
(Get back up.)

237
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:05,784
"Are you happy? I'm happy too."

238
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:06,619
Yu Jun.

239
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,587
"I'm happy too."

240
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:10,355
Yu Jun, I want to keep comforting you,

241
00:08:10,356 --> 00:08:12,958
but I just do not have any strength left.

242
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,961
I haven't worked out for a whole year.

243
00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:17,516
(HUENINGKAI and SOOBIN's creations)

244
00:08:17,517 --> 00:08:18,964
(They can't put off changing him
any longer.)

245
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:20,333
Sorry, Yu Jun.

246
00:08:20,334 --> 00:08:21,900
His clothes are very wet.

247
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,034
I know.

248
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:24,569
His clothes are damp.

249
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:25,436
All right. I won't do that.

250
00:08:25,437 --> 00:08:27,407
His body feels a bit hot.
I guess he really was hot.

251
00:08:27,607 --> 00:08:30,209
(Quickly getting his clothes off
to cool him down)

252
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:32,111
You're so adorable.

253
00:08:32,579 --> 00:08:33,479
How cute.

254
00:08:33,947 --> 00:08:35,080
They were really wet.

255
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:36,382
Want me to hold you again?

256
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:39,418
Okay, I will.

257
00:08:39,753 --> 00:08:41,287
It is cooler now.
Doesn't it feel a bit better?

258
00:08:41,721 --> 00:08:43,088
It's better, isn't it?

259
00:08:43,723 --> 00:08:45,157
It was pretty hot.

260
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,593
He already has defined rear deltoids.

261
00:08:48,594 --> 00:08:49,594
That's so random.

262
00:08:49,595 --> 00:08:52,097
(Naturally built)

263
00:08:52,098 --> 00:08:53,431
- You have muscles!
- His muscles...

264
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:54,567
Are we putting it on the right way?

265
00:08:54,734 --> 00:08:55,467
Yes.

266
00:08:55,468 --> 00:08:57,369
No, it's the other way around.

267
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,037
- This is the front.
- This is the back.

268
00:08:59,038 --> 00:08:59,971
- Like this?
- Yes.

269
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,974
We messed it up like that last time.

270
00:09:01,975 --> 00:09:04,143
Baby clothes don't have buttons
on the front.

271
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:06,178
Yu Jun, raise your arms.

272
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:07,212
- The airplane!
- Gosh.

273
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:10,184
(The T-shirt is going on now.)

274
00:09:10,185 --> 00:09:12,017
Bingo!

275
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:13,686
- Fingers.
- Fingers.

276
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:15,287
(Mid-tempo rhythm)

277
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:17,923
- The other arm.
- The other arm.

278
00:09:18,258 --> 00:09:20,092
(Top fitting completed to the rhythm)

279
00:09:20,093 --> 00:09:23,729
- Now, let him relax in nature.
- Isn't it nice and cool?

280
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,098
(Crying)

281
00:09:26,099 --> 00:09:26,999
All done.

282
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,433
- You're so loud.
- You look great.

283
00:09:28,434 --> 00:09:30,402
(Bottoms fitting completed too)

284
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:31,502
(Let's go look outside.)

285
00:09:31,539 --> 00:09:32,938
Do you feel better?

286
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,500
(He's been Yu Jun's airplane
for 40 minutes.)

287
00:09:35,501 --> 00:09:37,576
- He wants to look outside.
- He completely stopped crying.

288
00:09:37,711 --> 00:09:39,845
- Right.
- We should just let him look outside.

289
00:09:40,313 --> 00:09:42,948
Are you playing with your runny nose?

290
00:09:43,116 --> 00:09:44,650
It's dirty.

291
00:09:44,651 --> 00:09:46,085
(HUENINGKAI is bringing toilet paper.)

292
00:09:47,154 --> 00:09:49,288
Oh, dear. Are you upset?

293
00:09:49,289 --> 00:09:50,956
You must be very upset.

294
00:09:51,191 --> 00:09:54,160
I got it, Yu Jun. You must be sad.

295
00:09:54,161 --> 00:09:55,494
Okay. We won't wipe your nose.

296
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:56,762
It's also part of your charm.

297
00:09:57,063 --> 00:09:58,263
It's okay. Just wipe it with your hand.

298
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,132
Right. Everything you do is cute.

299
00:10:01,033 --> 00:10:02,133
Yu Jun.

300
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:03,600
Put him down so he can drink.

301
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,666
(They decide to hydrate the baby
on the floor.)

302
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:08,233
(Trying to put him down
after so many failed attempts)

303
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,733
(No! Pick me back up!)

304
00:10:11,866 --> 00:10:14,166
(He's clinging on with all his strength.)

305
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:16,800
(Pick me back up!)

306
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:20,966
(It's been 50 minutes...)

307
00:10:20,966 --> 00:10:24,000
(since BEOMGYU became a human airplane.)

308
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,333
(His eyes have lost their sparkle.)

309
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,700
Honestly, we haven't done anything.

310
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,933
BEOMGYU, your arms must be tired.

311
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:33,566
Get his attention!

312
00:10:33,866 --> 00:10:34,766
You want some food?

313
00:10:34,766 --> 00:10:36,566
(Trying to catch his attention with food)

314
00:10:36,566 --> 00:10:40,200
- Food?
- Food!

315
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,833
(It's a food festival!)

316
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:44,800
- Food!
- Food!

317
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,600
- Food!
- Food

318
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,766
(The main vocalist TAEHYUN's voice echoes
to the 14-month-old.)

319
00:10:49,766 --> 00:10:50,733
What was that?
Peek-a-boo!

320
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:53,933
(The baby has a front-row seat.)

321
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:55,033
Peek-a-boo!

322
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:56,833
Yu Jun, look.

323
00:10:56,966 --> 00:10:58,000
Peek-a-boo!

324
00:10:59,566 --> 00:11:01,033
(Yu Jun starts crying again
after the show.)

325
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:02,333
(Leaning in)

326
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,633
So cute!

327
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:04,783
(His cuteness could flatten the earth.)

328
00:11:04,784 --> 00:11:05,666
So cute.

329
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:07,133
Let him smell it.

330
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,600
(Trying to soothe him
with strawberry crackers)

331
00:11:10,966 --> 00:11:11,800
You like it?

332
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,066
(Give it to me now.)

333
00:11:13,066 --> 00:11:14,366
It looks yummy, right?

334
00:11:14,366 --> 00:11:16,533
(After getting his attention
with strawberry crackers)

335
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:19,200
Look at this. We have Legos!

336
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,266
It's okay, Yu Jun.

337
00:11:20,266 --> 00:11:21,866
Yu Jun, look!

338
00:11:21,866 --> 00:11:23,800
(Furious)

339
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,166
(He dances with the last bit
of energy he has left.)

340
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,700
(My private jet!)

341
00:11:29,366 --> 00:11:31,766
(Your private BEOMGYU jet is
no longer in service!)

342
00:11:32,266 --> 00:11:33,700
Yu Jun, who's your favorite?

343
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:35,933
It's Uncle BEOMGYU!

344
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:40,833
(BEOMGYU's energy level: 0 percent)

345
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:42,433
But this...

346
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:44,833
(Transfer spot: HUENINGKAI)

347
00:11:45,933 --> 00:11:47,833
- Good.
- That's not it.

348
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,366
Take him by the window.

349
00:11:50,266 --> 00:11:51,266
You like it?
Let's go by the window.

350
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,300
I love windows.

351
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,500
I think he's going to be okay.

352
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,766
- Are you calmer now?
- He'll be fine once he calms down.

353
00:11:59,766 --> 00:12:01,966
He'll be okay once he finishes crying.

354
00:12:01,966 --> 00:12:02,766
Right.

355
00:12:03,866 --> 00:12:04,733
Good job.

356
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:08,100
Even though Yu Jun couldn't really play,
he must be exhausted.

357
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,466
- I know.
- Well done.

358
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,933
Gosh. My biceps are pumped.

359
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,266
(He spots his favorite human bed.)

360
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:17,000
(I want to move.)

361
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,066
(You've reached your final destination.)

362
00:12:19,066 --> 00:12:20,566
That's it. Good.

363
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:23,566
Thank you.

364
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,000
- You're sad.
- Thanks.

365
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:28,866
Yu Jun, you don't even know
why you're crying, do you?

366
00:12:28,866 --> 00:12:30,900
I know. I don't think he knows either.

367
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:31,766
Oh, boy.

368
00:12:32,366 --> 00:12:33,833
Yu Jun, if you don't know
why you're crying,

369
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,333
how are we supposed to help you?

370
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:38,100
He's not crying because he's upset.

371
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:40,500
- He just wanted to cry.
- Right.

372
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,333
That happens.

373
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:44,433
I think it's better
if we go outside for a bit.

374
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:47,433
- Let's go out.
- I don't think he's happy here.

375
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:48,733
He's not happy.

376
00:12:48,733 --> 00:12:51,566
Let's take some rice crackers
just in case.

377
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,400
(Packing the diaper bag)

378
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,666
Let's go out.

379
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:56,133
Yu Jun, let's go out.

380
00:12:56,433 --> 00:12:57,933
Let's go for a walk, your favorite.

381
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,866
Baby's socks...

382
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,366
See you later.

383
00:13:01,366 --> 00:13:02,933
Yu Jun, see you later!

384
00:13:02,933 --> 00:13:04,700
Uncle TAEHYUN, goodbye.

385
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:05,566
Goodbye.

386
00:13:05,966 --> 00:13:08,000
- "Love you, Uncle!"
- Bye!

387
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,333
Love you!

388
00:13:09,766 --> 00:13:11,266
- Bye!
- Bye!

389
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,100
- See you.
- See you.

390
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:15,900
Yu Jun, say bye.
Let's walk. Your favorite...

391
00:13:16,966 --> 00:13:19,466
(Screaming)

392
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,133
(The scream of a rookie parent
who regained freedom after an hour.)

393
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,300
Uncle BEOMGYU is crying
because you left, Yu Jun.

394
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,333
He's crying, right?

395
00:13:35,366 --> 00:13:36,933
(Did he stop?)

396
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:39,633
(Nope.)

397
00:13:41,373 --> 00:13:44,207
(After all those hours,
he's become Yu Jun.)

398
00:13:45,666 --> 00:13:48,700
(11:40 a.m.: Yu Jun's walk)

399
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,266
Yu Jun, look, stairs.

400
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:51,700
Can you come down?

401
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,333
In 1, 2.

402
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,000
In 1, 2.

403
00:13:56,366 --> 00:13:58,966
You love it, don't you?

404
00:13:58,966 --> 00:14:00,133
He's walking.

405
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:03,400
How exciting.

406
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,966
(Yu Jun walks around excitedly.)

407
00:14:06,866 --> 00:14:12,200
If a baby cries
and asks to be held for no reason,

408
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:14,700
is it okay to leave him alone?

409
00:14:15,466 --> 00:14:16,300
You love it.

410
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:21,166
(Hold my hand.)

411
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:24,833
- HUENINGKAI, watch your shoelaces.
- Okay.

412
00:14:25,366 --> 00:14:26,200
Do you like being outside?

413
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:27,866
Yu Jun, are you happy?

414
00:14:27,866 --> 00:14:29,100
Yu Jun is happy now.

415
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,300
Let's help him...

416
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,600
- burn off his energy out here...
- Yes?

417
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,400
and feed him later.
Look how happy you are.

418
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,700
- So happy!
- So excited.

419
00:14:36,066 --> 00:14:37,533
Gosh. There's something like this.

420
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,333
A baby's cry is different depending
on whether they're hungry or sleepy.

421
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,100
How?

422
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,700
When they're hungry,
the volume gradually increases.

423
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:46,366
And they make sucking sounds.

424
00:14:46,366 --> 00:14:48,066
(Crying)

425
00:14:48,066 --> 00:14:49,666
(Screaming)

426
00:14:50,133 --> 00:14:51,900
I'm hungry

427
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:54,633
(BEOMGYU is overdoing it today.)

428
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:56,133
Aren't you tired?

429
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,700
Today is beautiful, right?

430
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:00,533
It's not cold, Yu Jun.

431
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:02,266
Yu Jun, look at this path.

432
00:15:02,266 --> 00:15:04,200
The cherry blossoms are so pretty.

433
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,366
Yu Jun, do you want to walk?

434
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,933
Do you want to walk here?

435
00:15:07,466 --> 00:15:09,133
How exciting.

436
00:15:09,133 --> 00:15:09,933
Yu Jun!

437
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:11,766
Look at the blossoms!

438
00:15:12,366 --> 00:15:15,466
- In 1, 2.
- That's it.

439
00:15:15,466 --> 00:15:18,766
In 1, 2.

440
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:22,400
- Yu Jun close-up!
- Yu Jun close-up.

441
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,166
You look so pretty!

442
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,200
Yes!

443
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,966
(After a happy walk)

444
00:15:28,966 --> 00:15:31,100
Yu Jun, where's Uncle TAEHYUN?

445
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,733
- There he is!
- Peek-a-boo!

446
00:15:34,466 --> 00:15:36,400
Yu Jun.

447
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,900
Are you hungry? Food?

448
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:38,800
Food time.

449
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,000
(12:00 p.m.: Lunchtime)

450
00:15:40,266 --> 00:15:42,800
- Let's sit him here.
- Let's use this chair.

451
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,500
Yu Jun, let's eat. Come here.

452
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,800
He won't cry if we put him here, right?

453
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:49,133
- That's right!
- Food!

454
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:51,766
- Good boy!
- So good!

455
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,233
- Open up!
- Say, ah.

456
00:15:53,233 --> 00:15:55,833
- That's it! What a good eater!
- Nice job!

457
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:56,733
Do you want to try this?

458
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:59,700
Yu Jun likes to feed himself with a spoon.

459
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:01,166
Let him hold it.

460
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:02,633
(Giving Yu Jun his spoon)

461
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:03,733
Can you eat by yourself?

462
00:16:06,266 --> 00:16:07,333
He's good.

463
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:08,833
- Let me wash my hands first.
- Go ahead.

464
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:11,033
You're so good!

465
00:16:11,566 --> 00:16:12,533
Is it good?

466
00:16:13,466 --> 00:16:16,100
That's it! You're so good!

467
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,166
Food?

468
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:20,366
(Yu Jun gets excited
after eating something delicious.)

469
00:16:20,366 --> 00:16:21,866
Say, ah.

470
00:16:21,866 --> 00:16:23,100
(Opening wide)

471
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:24,333
That's it!

472
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:26,033
He's using the spoon so well.

473
00:16:26,566 --> 00:16:27,700
Was he happy outside?

474
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,700
Yes, way happier.
He basically ran.

475
00:16:29,566 --> 00:16:30,933
- Really?
- He ran around.

476
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:33,600
Hey, look at you!

477
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,566
I didn't know you were such a good eater.

478
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:39,366
What a good boy!

479
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,300
It's so yummy!

480
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:43,900
- Love you.
- Thank you.

481
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:44,833
You're so good.

482
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,500
We should always put him
in a chair to eat.

483
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,900
(The uncles' lunch is ramyeon.)

484
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,200
(Tired)

485
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,933
- Food?
- Yes, food.

486
00:16:50,933 --> 00:16:53,833
(Yu Jun starts to fuss again
after a while.)

487
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,966
- I'll pick you up when you're done.
- I'll pick you up when you're done.

488
00:16:55,966 --> 00:16:57,600
It's only been two days,

489
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:00,400
but I think
I'm getting used to his crying.

490
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,333
We need to get used to it.

491
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,400
Right. When he cries, he cries.

492
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:06,433
(Roaring)

493
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:08,133
(Big lions competing
over the baby's food.)

494
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,766
(What's going on?)

495
00:17:09,766 --> 00:17:11,700
(I'll eat your food!)

496
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,600
(It's mine!)

497
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,900
That's it!

498
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:18,333
- Say, ah!
- Open up!

499
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,433
(Parenting means
never stopping the sound effects.)

500
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:23,233
- That's it. Good boy!
- Yummy!

501
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:24,733
- It's so good!
- So good.

502
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:25,800
You're so good.

503
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:29,733
(They keep feeding him
while making constant sounds.)

504
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,400
- That's it! Good boy!
- Good boy.

505
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,933
- Food.
- Here comes the food.

506
00:17:34,933 --> 00:17:36,200
Your food is here.

507
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,800
You ate so neatly.

508
00:17:38,066 --> 00:17:40,466
(Showing off white teeth to make him eat)

509
00:17:40,466 --> 00:17:41,700
(I can do that too.)

510
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:44,466
Yu Jun, chew first, then open your mouth.

511
00:17:44,466 --> 00:17:46,366
You opened it right away?

512
00:17:46,366 --> 00:17:47,800
You're such a good eater.

513
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,066
What a good boy.

514
00:17:49,066 --> 00:17:50,133
I think YEONJUN is in trouble.

515
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,400
We'll get close to him first.

516
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,600
YEONJUN never had a chance.

517
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,266
(He opens his mouth like a baby bird.)

518
00:17:55,266 --> 00:17:56,500
What a good boy.

519
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:59,066
- How are you so good at this?
- How?

520
00:17:59,066 --> 00:18:00,000
Looks delicious.

521
00:18:00,966 --> 00:18:02,333
Guys, the ramyeon is ready.

522
00:18:02,766 --> 00:18:04,200
It looks amazing.

523
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,000
We're going to eat too!

524
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,666
Let's see who eats better!

525
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,433
(He carefully lifts the noodles.)

526
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:10,833
(What's that?)

527
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,900
- That's it.
- Good boy.

528
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:13,700
Can I eat too?
SOOBIN.

529
00:18:14,666 --> 00:18:16,366
Say, ah!

530
00:18:16,366 --> 00:18:17,800
I won't let you win.

531
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,400
- You're going to lose, Yu Jun.
- SOOBIN is too good!

532
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,733
Open wide!

533
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:23,133
That's it.

534
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:25,266
(Yu Jun is so adorable.)

535
00:18:25,266 --> 00:18:26,533
He said, "Ah."

536
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:27,733
How adorable.

537
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:28,633
It's really delicious.

538
00:18:29,266 --> 00:18:30,900
If it's this salty, it can't be bad.

539
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,000
But why is it so salty?

540
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,366
Should I add more water?

541
00:18:33,366 --> 00:18:34,300
It's too salty.

542
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:37,333
- Yu Jun, say, ah.
- Open up. Good job.

543
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:40,866
(The baby bird Yu Jun's
appetite explodes today.)

544
00:18:40,866 --> 00:18:42,666
Yu Jun, you're such a good baby.

545
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:44,333
So yummy! Great job.

546
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:46,500
Maybe this is...

547
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,000
- Seriously.
- why people have kids.

548
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,067
This is what I love about parenting.

549
00:18:49,068 --> 00:18:51,300
When they listen, you're so happy.

550
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:52,666
When they don't, you're exhausted.

551
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:56,366
But watching him is healing.

552
00:18:56,366 --> 00:18:57,133
You too, SOOBIN.

553
00:18:57,133 --> 00:18:58,366
I added more water.

554
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,000
- You don't want any, HUENINGKAI?
- No, thanks.

555
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,666
Say, ah!

556
00:19:03,066 --> 00:19:05,233
- Open up.
- That's it!

557
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,733
Last bite. You've eaten so much!

558
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:08,266
Goodness. Yu Jun!

559
00:19:08,266 --> 00:19:09,833
You'll grow up to be 186 cm.

560
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,366
I know. What if he grows taller than us?

561
00:19:11,366 --> 00:19:12,633
Like up to 190 cm.

562
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:13,666
That would be upsetting.

563
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,500
Yu Jun, last bite. Open up.

564
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,500
"Guys, thanks for taking
such good care of me back then."

565
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:19,133
"Sometimes I watch the show too."

566
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:20,833
And he's like 190 cm tall.
Yummy!

567
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:22,766
"What have you been up to?"

568
00:19:22,766 --> 00:19:24,600
- "I'm a basketball player."
- You're so good.

569
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,400
He slapped me.
(Here I come for revenge!)

570
00:19:26,966 --> 00:19:29,066
(After a relaxed lunchtime...)

571
00:19:29,066 --> 00:19:30,300
More?

572
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,333
- Should we give him a rice cracker?
- A rice cracker?

573
00:19:33,266 --> 00:19:35,100
Okay. This smells great.

574
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:36,266
That's it. You like it?

575
00:19:36,266 --> 00:19:37,366
Good job.

576
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:39,266
- So happy.
- He's such a good eater.

577
00:19:39,266 --> 00:19:40,633
He loves it so much.

578
00:19:40,633 --> 00:19:41,600
Delicious.

579
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:42,666
Where's the lotion?

580
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:43,666
Okay.

581
00:19:44,366 --> 00:19:45,233
He wants to get down, right?

582
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:46,733
That's it.

583
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,466
(Lifting him up)

584
00:19:48,466 --> 00:19:51,166
That's it. Good boy.

585
00:19:52,066 --> 00:19:53,166
Do you want to look?

586
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:54,166
What a nice breeze.

587
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:56,233
(This is the life.)

588
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:58,600
Do you want to go there? Good.

589
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:01,133
(They hurry to eat ramyeon
so they can switch at any time.)

590
00:20:01,828 --> 00:20:03,295
(Winking)

591
00:20:04,264 --> 00:20:05,899
How did BEOMGYU hold him for 20 minutes?

592
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,433
(The old airplane has no fuel left.)

593
00:20:07,434 --> 00:20:08,133
How did he do it?

594
00:20:09,269 --> 00:20:10,169
Do you want to play airplane?

595
00:20:10,437 --> 00:20:11,604
(Here comes a new airplane.)

596
00:20:11,605 --> 00:20:13,639
(Lifting)

597
00:20:13,741 --> 00:20:16,175
He likes it.

598
00:20:16,176 --> 00:20:17,043
He's enjoying it.

599
00:20:17,044 --> 00:20:18,411
(When you're watching a child,
you have to react even while eating.)

600
00:20:18,817 --> 00:20:19,711
(This is fun!)

601
00:20:19,712 --> 00:20:21,480
(It's so much fun!)

602
00:20:21,782 --> 00:20:23,182
(I'm excited too.)

603
00:20:23,249 --> 00:20:24,383
How cute.

604
00:20:24,384 --> 00:20:25,484
(A smile brings good luck.)

605
00:20:25,652 --> 00:20:26,885
Let me wash that for you.

606
00:20:27,287 --> 00:20:30,423
Could you rinse his mouth...

607
00:20:30,424 --> 00:20:31,624
and wash his hands?

608
00:20:31,825 --> 00:20:34,093
(Mission: Rinse around Yu Jun's mouth)

609
00:20:34,094 --> 00:20:34,927
Wipe!

610
00:20:35,462 --> 00:20:36,328
(Wiping)

611
00:20:37,097 --> 00:20:38,230
That's smart.

612
00:20:38,231 --> 00:20:40,032
(Wiping)

613
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:41,867
(TAEHYUN gained a skill.)

614
00:20:41,868 --> 00:20:42,901
(Touching)

615
00:20:42,902 --> 00:20:44,570
- He's so cute.
- It's nice!

616
00:20:44,571 --> 00:20:45,637
- Good!
- He's so soft.

617
00:20:46,101 --> 00:20:47,240
- Nice.
- Nice.

618
00:20:47,241 --> 00:20:48,207
How nice.

619
00:20:48,210 --> 00:20:49,875
Good boy. Hold my hand.

620
00:20:49,876 --> 00:20:51,612
- It's nice.
- Nice.

621
00:20:51,613 --> 00:20:53,245
It's a lot better.

622
00:20:53,747 --> 00:20:54,680
How nice.

623
00:20:55,249 --> 00:20:57,249
It's so secure to hold him
with both hands.

624
00:20:57,951 --> 00:20:59,351
I think I could do this for an hour.

625
00:20:59,486 --> 00:21:01,020
- Like that.
- Supporting him with both hands?

626
00:21:01,021 --> 00:21:02,455
- Yes.
- But if you do that,

627
00:21:02,456 --> 00:21:03,622
Yu Jun will keep leaning back.

628
00:21:03,623 --> 00:21:05,591
That's why I'm leaning back.

629
00:21:05,592 --> 00:21:06,625
It's better this way.

630
00:21:07,060 --> 00:21:08,460
That might be bad for your back.

631
00:21:08,461 --> 00:21:10,295
(Remember, back surgery is
30,000 dollars.)

632
00:21:10,296 --> 00:21:10,996
(Burping)

633
00:21:11,898 --> 00:21:12,764
(Burping)

634
00:21:12,765 --> 00:21:15,834
(Suddenly making EDM sounds)

635
00:21:17,437 --> 00:21:20,272
(The uncles start entertaining Yu Jun.)

636
00:21:22,943 --> 00:21:23,776
He's excited.
(Busy eating ramyeon)

637
00:21:24,745 --> 00:21:25,478
It's fun.

638
00:21:26,646 --> 00:21:28,113
(Passing Yu Jun over)

639
00:21:28,114 --> 00:21:29,481
(One)

640
00:21:29,482 --> 00:21:31,016
(Two)

641
00:21:31,017 --> 00:21:32,551
(Three)

642
00:21:32,552 --> 00:21:34,620
- You like it, don't you? It's fun.
- He's happy.

643
00:21:34,621 --> 00:21:35,454
Mama!

644
00:21:35,455 --> 00:21:39,658
(Now HUENINGKAI can relax
and eat ramyeon.)

645
00:21:41,228 --> 00:21:42,295
Look down there.

646
00:21:43,163 --> 00:21:44,363
Look outside.

647
00:21:45,632 --> 00:21:48,500
(Making playful sounds)

648
00:21:48,501 --> 00:21:49,368
(Babbling)

649
00:21:50,804 --> 00:21:53,739
(Secure)

650
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:54,573
Mama!

651
00:21:56,076 --> 00:21:57,043
(Uncle, that over there!)

652
00:21:58,812 --> 00:21:59,678
Are you having fun?

653
00:21:59,679 --> 00:22:01,580
(Playing with the intercom)

654
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:07,678
(Waltzing with Carrot Uncle)

655
00:22:09,189 --> 00:22:10,122
Is it fun?

656
00:22:10,123 --> 00:22:11,292
(Walking around holding Yu Jun)

657
00:22:11,293 --> 00:22:12,793
Is this fun?

658
00:22:12,794 --> 00:22:13,692
(A perfect bounce)

659
00:22:13,693 --> 00:22:14,860
Yu Jun, are you having fun?

660
00:22:14,861 --> 00:22:15,995
(Comfortable)

661
00:22:15,996 --> 00:22:16,902
You want to go down?

662
00:22:18,565 --> 00:22:19,632
(Succeeded in putting him down)

663
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:20,432
What do you need?

664
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:21,967
Hooray!

665
00:22:22,803 --> 00:22:24,237
Yu Jun is walking well.

666
00:22:25,071 --> 00:22:26,805
We haven't seen him walking
at home in a while.

667
00:22:26,806 --> 00:22:29,741
(So, we walked along with him!)

668
00:22:29,742 --> 00:22:31,610
- Yu Jun, I love you.
- HUENINGKAI, where's my phone?

669
00:22:31,611 --> 00:22:32,778
(I don't want to do that.)

670
00:22:32,779 --> 00:22:35,213
(Trying to take pictures of Yu Jun
for himself)

671
00:22:35,214 --> 00:22:37,015
- Yu Jun, look here.
- Look at me.

672
00:22:37,016 --> 00:22:38,984
- Yu Jun, I love you.
- Look at me once.

673
00:22:38,985 --> 00:22:40,452
- I love you.
- I love you.

674
00:22:40,453 --> 00:22:42,854
- I love you.
- Yu Jun, I love you.

675
00:22:42,855 --> 00:22:44,122
Look at me once.

676
00:22:44,358 --> 00:22:45,525
Let me take a picture of you.

677
00:22:45,526 --> 00:22:46,425
(SOOBIN sliding on his knees)

678
00:22:46,426 --> 00:22:48,327
- "Uncle, I love you."
- Yu Jun.

679
00:22:48,562 --> 00:22:49,962
Yu Jun, I love you.

680
00:22:49,963 --> 00:22:51,430
"Uncle, I love you."

681
00:22:51,431 --> 00:22:52,365
(I love you, too!)
That's adorable.

682
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:57,003
(A big endorphin boost!)

683
00:22:57,004 --> 00:22:58,538
- I love you.
- Yu Jun.

684
00:22:58,638 --> 00:23:00,272
Yu Jun, I love you.

685
00:23:00,674 --> 00:23:01,741
I love you.

686
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,547
- Yu Jun.
- He's got something.

687
00:23:09,683 --> 00:23:11,083
What is this?

688
00:23:11,084 --> 00:23:12,518
(Appearing with a new toy)

689
00:23:12,519 --> 00:23:13,319
You're strong.

690
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:14,854
(Yu Jun seems interested.)

691
00:23:14,855 --> 00:23:15,755
(Hold my hand.)

692
00:23:15,756 --> 00:23:17,456
- He wants you to hold his hand.
- I'll buy something.

693
00:23:17,457 --> 00:23:19,692
(Pushing the cart with Uncle SOOBIN)

694
00:23:19,693 --> 00:23:22,094
(Bending over for Yu Jun)

695
00:23:22,095 --> 00:23:23,863
(A wheel falls off.)

696
00:23:23,864 --> 00:23:25,765
(Emergency! A wheel came off!)

697
00:23:25,766 --> 00:23:27,299
We can put it back together.

698
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,768
It's F1.

699
00:23:28,935 --> 00:23:29,835
Pit stop!

700
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:32,205
(F1 X TOGETHER is rushing
so Yu Jun doesn't cry.)

701
00:23:32,206 --> 00:23:34,407
- Done.
- He's getting in our way, right?

702
00:23:34,408 --> 00:23:35,875
Let's go!

703
00:23:35,876 --> 00:23:37,076
(They put it back before Yu Jun cries.)

704
00:23:39,679 --> 00:23:40,846
Uncle BEOMGYU stole it.

705
00:23:41,248 --> 00:23:42,281
That looks fun.

706
00:23:42,282 --> 00:23:43,516
(From airplane captain to cart rider)

707
00:23:43,517 --> 00:23:44,851
Suddenly, this is so interesting.

708
00:23:45,118 --> 00:23:46,919
He's running at full speed now...

709
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:47,686
because he lost his cart.

710
00:23:48,121 --> 00:23:49,922
Give it back to me!

711
00:23:49,923 --> 00:23:51,289
(If you get caught,
you're in big trouble.)

712
00:23:51,290 --> 00:23:54,026
You should've slowed down
and let him take over at some point.

713
00:23:54,027 --> 00:23:55,160
(This is not fair!)

714
00:23:55,996 --> 00:23:57,162
(He ends up giving it back.)

715
00:23:57,163 --> 00:23:57,930
He's rubbing his eyes.

716
00:23:58,732 --> 00:23:59,632
My back hurts.

717
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,067
My back is hurting.

718
00:24:01,068 --> 00:24:02,301
(The price for stealing the cart)

719
00:24:03,003 --> 00:24:04,971
Let's go!

720
00:24:05,505 --> 00:24:07,072
To Uncle HUENINGKAI!

721
00:24:07,474 --> 00:24:08,274
Crash!

722
00:24:08,441 --> 00:24:10,008
(Full-on acting)

723
00:24:11,611 --> 00:24:12,411
I'm dead!
Okay.

724
00:24:14,614 --> 00:24:15,681
- That's cute.
- He wants his hand.

725
00:24:16,082 --> 00:24:17,349
Turn left.

726
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,051
There's a really ugly uncle over there.

727
00:24:19,552 --> 00:24:20,752
Let me catch Yu Jun!

728
00:24:20,753 --> 00:24:22,821
(Take down the bleached-hair monster!)

729
00:24:22,822 --> 00:24:23,722
- Let's beat him.
- Yu Jun!

730
00:24:23,723 --> 00:24:25,090
In 1, 2, 3.

731
00:24:25,592 --> 00:24:27,860
(We beat the blonde monster!)

732
00:24:28,003 --> 00:24:29,628
He finds it entertaining.

733
00:24:29,629 --> 00:24:31,564
Should I go get Yu Jun?

734
00:24:31,565 --> 00:24:34,166
- This is entertaining for me too.
- Yu Jun.

735
00:24:34,401 --> 00:24:35,267
Yu Jun!

736
00:24:35,735 --> 00:24:37,402
(We beat the blond monster again!)

737
00:24:37,403 --> 00:24:38,537
(Fully committed to his acting)

738
00:24:38,538 --> 00:24:40,506
- He really likes it.
- He's loving it.

739
00:24:40,941 --> 00:24:42,141
He finds it funny.

740
00:24:42,676 --> 00:24:44,209
Let's go.

741
00:24:44,210 --> 00:24:45,043
(To the next quest!)

742
00:24:46,513 --> 00:24:47,947
Crash!

743
00:24:47,948 --> 00:24:49,114
(Yu Jun and Uncle SOOBIN are training.)

744
00:24:49,115 --> 00:24:49,882
He's enjoying himself.

745
00:24:50,016 --> 00:24:51,249
He's having fun.

746
00:24:51,250 --> 00:24:53,719
(I'm going to get stronger!)

747
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:55,620
Yu Jun, it's the monster.

748
00:24:56,389 --> 00:24:58,250
(One shot, one kill)

749
00:24:58,251 --> 00:24:59,457
(Yu Jun is stronger after training.)

750
00:24:59,458 --> 00:25:00,359
He had a big laugh.

751
00:25:00,994 --> 00:25:02,995
Yu Jun, there they are.

752
00:25:03,563 --> 00:25:04,730
Crash!

753
00:25:04,731 --> 00:25:05,564
(One shot, two kills)

754
00:25:06,166 --> 00:25:07,218
(I'm a really strong 14-month-old.)

755
00:25:07,219 --> 00:25:08,801
- He's cute.
- He's smiling.

756
00:25:08,802 --> 00:25:10,469
- Hey, you're up.
- Okay.

757
00:25:10,603 --> 00:25:11,469
My back hurts.

758
00:25:11,604 --> 00:25:12,904
Let's go.

759
00:25:12,905 --> 00:25:14,606
(Two members hurt their backs.)

760
00:25:15,008 --> 00:25:15,975
(I can't do it anymore.)
What do we do?

761
00:25:17,210 --> 00:25:19,377
(HUENINGKAI takes over after SOOBIN.)

762
00:25:19,378 --> 00:25:20,279
Come beat me.

763
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:21,580
Yu Jun, shall we go crash?

764
00:25:21,748 --> 00:25:22,815
There's Uncle TAEHYUN.

765
00:25:22,816 --> 00:25:23,716
Crash!

766
00:25:24,384 --> 00:25:26,284
(Yu Jun beat the monster again!)

767
00:25:26,285 --> 00:25:27,786
- Good job. How fun!
- It's fun.

768
00:25:27,787 --> 00:25:29,021
This is fun!

769
00:25:29,623 --> 00:25:31,924
(He spots a black-haired monster ahead.)

770
00:25:35,161 --> 00:25:37,462
(It's fun defeating them.)

771
00:25:37,463 --> 00:25:39,064
(Now only the Leader Monster is left.)

772
00:25:39,065 --> 00:25:39,698
Crash!

773
00:25:39,699 --> 00:25:40,932
(Grunting)

774
00:25:41,534 --> 00:25:42,434
Look at Yu Jun.

775
00:25:42,570 --> 00:25:43,802
(Is it you who beat me?)

776
00:25:43,803 --> 00:25:45,571
(Facing each other)

777
00:25:45,939 --> 00:25:46,805
He's happy.

778
00:25:46,806 --> 00:25:47,940
(Today's quest is complete!)

779
00:25:47,941 --> 00:25:49,275
A 14-month-old is stronger...

780
00:25:49,276 --> 00:25:52,044
than four adult men combined.

781
00:25:53,246 --> 00:25:56,415
- You're sleepy, Yu Jun.
- You're sleepy.

782
00:25:56,416 --> 00:25:57,382
You're sleepy.
(They're hoping he's sleepy.)

783
00:25:58,284 --> 00:25:59,318
Yu Jun, aren't you sleepy?

784
00:25:59,753 --> 00:26:00,819
BEOMGYU is.

785
00:26:01,154 --> 00:26:02,154
(I'm not sleepy!)

786
00:26:02,155 --> 00:26:03,322
I wish he said,

787
00:26:03,323 --> 00:26:05,090
"Guys, I want to take a nap now."

788
00:26:05,592 --> 00:26:06,859
"Wake me up in two hours."

789
00:26:06,860 --> 00:26:08,360
I wish he would say that and go to sleep.

790
00:26:08,361 --> 00:26:10,596
I hope he yawns once for us.

791
00:26:11,036 --> 00:26:11,800
Seriously.
